# 1. Ignore absolutely everything by default
*

# 2. Un-ignore all directories so Git can actually traverse your project
!*/

# 3. Explicitly BLACKLIST heavy/unwanted directories 
# (This stops Git from finding and tracking .py or .txt files hidden inside these)
venv/
data/
bitsandbytes/
*checkpoints*/
jp*/
__pycache__/
.*

# 4. Whitelist the specific file extensions you actually want to track
!*.py
!*.sh
!*.txt

# 5. Make sure the gitignore itself is tracked
!.gitignore

Pretrain/Log*.txt
